Vegetable Masala

2 potatoes -- peeled and cubed
1 carrot -- chopped
10 French-style green beans -- chopped
1 quarts cold water
1/2  cup  frozen green peas -- thawed
1  teaspoons  salt
1/2  teaspoons  ground turmeric
1  tablespoons  vegetable oil
1  teaspoons  mustard seed
1  teaspoons  ground cumin
1 onion -- finely chopped
2 tomatoes - blanched -- peeled and chopped
1  teaspoons  garam masala
1/2  teaspoons  ground ginger
1/2  teaspoons  garlic powder
1/2  teaspoons  chili powder
1 sprig cilantro leaves -- for garnish

Place potatoes, carrots and green beans in the cold water. Allow to soak
while you prepare the rest of the vegetables; drain.  In a microwave safe
dish place the potatoes, carrots, green beans, peas, salt and turmeric.
Cook for 8 minutes.  Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Cook
mustard seeds and cumin; when seeds start to sputter and pop, add the
onion and saute until transparent. Stir in the tomatoes, garam masala,
ginger, garlic and chili powder; saute 3 minutes. Add the cooked
vegetables to the tomato mixture and saute 1 minute.  Garnish with
cilantro leaves.

Recipe Notes
&quot;Masala means a spicy mixture. Vegetable masala is a mixture of vegetables
like potatoes, carrots, peas and beans cooked with onions &amp; tomatoes
adding spices like garam masala powder, ginger and garlic powder.&quot;

